---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Terms — DOKU">
  <div class="narrow">
    <div class="page-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Before you claim one</div>
      <h1 class="serif">Terms</h1>
      <p>What governs using this site and claiming an object through it. Written to be read, not skimmed past.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Who this agreement is with</h2>
      <p>This site is operated by DOKU. Registered business name and address: <span class="legal-fill">[[fill]]</span> — added here once business registration is finalized. By using the site, you're agreeing to these terms with that entity.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>What DOKU is</h2>
      <p>DOKU is a marketplace for one-of-one objects. Every item exists exactly once — we don't manufacture, commission, or restock. When an object is claimed, that listing closes for good.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Browsing and accounts</h2>
      <p>Browsing the collection and holding items in your cart don't require an account. Completing a purchase does — we use a passwordless sign-in (a link emailed to you, no password to manage or lose).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Prices and currency</h2>
      <p>Prices are shown converted into your local currency for convenience only. The charge itself is always calculated and processed in Indian Rupees (INR), from the object's real listed price — the currency you see is a display, not a quote.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Payment</h2>
      <p>Payments are processed by Razorpay. We currently accept domestic (India) payment methods in INR. Card details are entered directly into Razorpay's secure checkout — DOKU never sees or stores them.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>What a claim means</h2>
      <p>A verified payment reserves the object under your name. We confirm the order and ship it to you personally — see <a href="/refund-policy">Refunds &amp; Cancellations</a> and <a href="/shipping">Shipping</a> for what happens between reservation and delivery.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>The objects themselves</h2>
      <p>Every listing is described and, where photographed, shown as accurately as we can manage. Unsourced items carry a hand-drawn sketch instead of a photo, never an image of something we don't yet hold. Once an object is claimed, it will not be restocked, reissued, or offered again in any form.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>The DOKU name, the site's design, its photography and sketches, and its written content belong to DOKU. Nothing here may be reproduced or reused without our written permission.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>We take care in how we describe, photograph, and ship each object, but we can't guarantee the site will be error-free or uninterrupted. To the extent the law allows, DOKU isn't liable for indirect or consequential loss arising from your use of the site.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>We may update these terms as the site and its policies evolve. The date below reflects the last change.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>These terms are governed by the laws of India, and any dispute is subject to the jurisdiction of its courts.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="fine-print">Questions about any of this — <a href="/inquire">Inquire</a> reaches a person, not a form processor.</p>

    <div class="legal-updated">Last updated 17 July 2026</div>
  </div>
</Base>
